description.displayText: Josefina was a wonderful aid for my elderly parents. She was dependable, kind and extremely professional. She worked hard and kept a very good line of communication. I would highly recommend her to anyone.

description.displayText: Josefina is an honest, dependable, kind, and compassionate caregiver. She stayed overnight to care for my father (late 70s, dementia), assisting with food prep, feeding, clothes changing, medicine giving, and companionship. She has her own transportation to/from the job. She kept a perfect line of communication open with me while she was there. I would hire again without hesitation in the future. I would recommend that, if given the opportunity, you do the same as well. She is an absolute gift of a human being and your loved ones would be in great hands.

description.displayText: Josefina is a caring professional who helped me while healing from a shoulder replacement before I regained use of the arm/hand. I will definitely hire her again when funds allow.  I recommend her highly. Josefina gives 110% to everything she does. I feel safe when she helped me bathe. She helped me with everything one can't do without two working hands -- fix my hair, change sheets on the bed, shower, shampoo, clean bathroom, laundry -- she has my highest esteem and recommendation. She is punctual and dependable. Josefina doesn't mind taking you food shopping, unlike many other HHAs.
